<paragraph blockId="26.[254,1242,1166,1988]" box="[305,1115,1488,1527]" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Geographic distribution. Type locality only.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[254,1242,1166,1988]" box="[305,1019,1534,1574]" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Geological age. Middle or late Visean.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[254,1242,1166,1988]" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">
.Etymology. Derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[957,1076,1581,1620]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">parvus</emphasis>
meaning mmute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[254,1242,1166,1988]" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[514,866,1673,1712]" class="Gastropoda" genus="Microcochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="parva" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[514,866,1673,1712]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Microcochlis parva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[900,978,1673,1712]" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[254,649,1720,1758]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eucochlidae" genus="Eucochlis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Vetigastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="umbiliparva" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[254,649,1720,1758]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Eucochlis umbiliparva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[672,748,1720,1758]" pageId="26" pageNumber="89" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having a smaller shell, short blunt protoconch and prominent spiral rows of pustu!es. 
<figureCitation box="[432,600,1811,1851]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[333,389,3138,3176]" captionTargetBox="[312,1966,425,3012]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Distribution of Carboniferous outcrop and examined localities," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4654601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4654601/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Figures 1</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[717,735,1811,1851]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[383,440,3170,3206]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Stratigraphic nomenclature." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657280" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657280/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">2</figureCitation>
~n 
<figureCitation box="[821,972,1811,1851]" captionStart="Plate 12" captionStartId="46.[378,460,2539,2576]" captionTargetBox="[501,1959,423,2484]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="Plate 12. Figs 1-5. Microcochlis parva n.gen., n.sp. l. Paratype, apertura1 view lA mm x l.2 mm (F78438a). 2. Paratype, apertural view l.3 mm x l.0 mm (F78438b). 3. Holotype, apertural view 2.1 mm x l.5 mm (F78437). 4. Oblique apical view, protoconch and early stage of teleoconch of Fig. l. 5. Apical view. Locality 24. Figs 6-1l. Kyndalynia inflata n.gen., n.sp. 6. Paratype, apertural view, slightly tilted forward 1.1 mm x l.0 mm (F78441a). 7. Holotype, side view, height l.3 mm (F78440). 8. Paratype, apertural view 1.0 mm x l.0 mm (F78442). 9. Paratype, apertural view 1.2 mm x l.0 mm (F78443). 10. Paratype, apertural view, slightly tilted forward 1.1 mm x 1.0 mm (F78441b). 1l. Protoconch of holotype. Locality 24. Bar scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4654633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4654633/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="89">Plate 12</figureCitation>
are juveniles, showmg an arched whorl profile and only faint expression of spiral cords. The spiral angulation begins to appear at 2~ whorls.
</paragraph>
